''(Biology)'' When referring to a single single strand of [[nucleic acid]] which is used as the template for DNA replication. Consider the following single stranded DNA molecule (on the bottom) undergoing replication (the direction of synthesis is indicated by an arrow):

      5' |------>      | 3'   newly synthesized strand
      3' |------------ | 5'   template (positive sense) strand

Replication of the positive sense strand occurs to produce a double stranded DNA molecule.


''Compare with [[negative sense]].''

